00:02:56,385 --> 00:03:00,389
So we're planning our next vacation.
I want Australia, she wants Italy.

3
00:03:00,556 --> 00:03:04,393
I like snorkeling.
She likes garlic.

4
00:03:04,560 --> 00:03:08,814
All of a sudden, out of nowhere,
she says to me: "do I need her?"

5
00:03:09,857 --> 00:03:12,443
Jesus, Benny.
What kind of a question is that?

6
00:03:12,610 --> 00:03:15,946
Need?
What does it really mean to need somebody?

7
00:03:16,113 --> 00:03:18,240
Benny, fuel line.

8
00:03:19,950 --> 00:03:22,161
Waldo, could you answer that phone?

9
00:03:24,079 --> 00:03:27,082
- Hello.
- I need a check, Benny. COD.

10
00:03:27,249 --> 00:03:29,460
In a minute.
Meet me in the office.

11
00:03:29,627 --> 00:03:31,629
All right.

12
00:03:31,795 --> 00:03:34,882
Put that out!
I got a fuel line broke.

13
00:03:35,049 --> 00:03:37,968
Hey, Benny.
Joon's on the phone again.

14
00:03:38,135 --> 00:03:40,804
I'll call back.
Find out what she wants.

15
00:03:40,971 --> 00:03:43,140
It's an emergency.

16
00:03:43,307 --> 00:03:46,393
She says you're runnin' low
on Peanut Butter Super Chunks.

17
00:03:48,395 --> 00:03:50,481
An emergency...

18
00:03:55,110 --> 00:03:58,989
The issue is jelly.
You only like two kinds.

19
00:04:01,242 --> 00:04:05,162
You either like grape or boysenberry.
Which is it? All right.

20
00:04:05,329 --> 00:04:07,665
Yeah, yeah, yeah, peanut butter.
I know. Super Crunch.

21
00:04:07,831 --> 00:04:10,668
I'll see you at six, OK?
Bye.

22
00:04:12,294 --> 00:04:14,296
Thanks for waitin', ma'am.

23
00:04:14,463 --> 00:04:17,716
I'm afraid the best
we can do for you is gonna be...

24
00:04:19,176 --> 00:04:20,928
It's gonna be $750.

25
00:04:21,595 --> 00:04:24,174
If you check around, you'll see that
that is a really good deal.

26
00:04:24,198 --> 00:04:25,140
Yeah?

27
00:04:25,307 --> 00:04:27,559
That is a really very good deal, ma'am.

28
00:04:28,477 --> 00:04:31,063
A little too good.

29
00:04:33,107 --> 00:04:34,858
Let's do it.

30
00:04:50,457 --> 00:04:52,543
Come here.
Come here.

31
00:05:03,595 --> 00:05:06,765
You're not doing your job!
What is your job, anyway?

32
00:05:06,932 --> 00:05:09,393
To clean this house, but not any more!

33
00:05:09,560 --> 00:05:11,020
Get out of my sight!

34
00:05:11,186 --> 00:05:13,397
You wouldn't dare, Joon!

35
00:05:15,733 --> 00:05:18,068
What is going on here?
Joon?

36
00:05:18,235 --> 00:05:21,113
Mrs. Smail, please, let me explain.

37
00:05:21,280 --> 00:05:24,074
Beware, the winds of reason
shall blow stern.

38
00:05:24,241 --> 00:05:26,243
- What?
- I'm done, Mr. Pearl.

39
00:05:26,410 --> 00:05:28,579
I'm done!
The mule's turned to glue!

40
00:05:28,746 --> 00:05:32,166
She wanders off unescorted.
She has sudden outbursts.

41
00:05:32,333 --> 00:05:34,418
She's simply unmanageable.

42
00:05:35,252 --> 00:05:37,921
Mrs. Smail, wait.
Please, let me talk to her.

43
00:05:38,088 --> 00:05:41,675
I can talk to her.
You can't quit on such short notice.

44
00:05:41,842 --> 00:05:44,470
I'm sorry, sir.
In Ireland, we have a sayin'.

45
00:05:44,636 --> 00:05:47,765
"When a boat runs ashore,
the sea has spoken."

46
00:05:51,101 --> 00:05:53,896
<i>Come on!
We can't play three-handed poker.</i>

47
00:05:54,063 --> 00:05:58,484
She's gonna be alone every day.
I'm not leavin' her alone at night, too.

48
00:05:58,650 --> 00:06:00,861
<i>So bring her.
She just paints and reads.</i>

49
00:06:01,028 --> 00:06:03,447
Yeah, and lights things on fire.

50
00:06:03,614 --> 00:06:07,076
<i>That happened once.
I got a fire extinguisher. Just bring her.</i>

51
00:06:07,242 --> 00:06:10,954
Get your ass over here.
Don't forget the Louis Prima record.

52
00:06:11,121 --> 00:06:13,207
Remember, always play for keeps.

53
00:06:13,374 --> 00:06:17,169
All right, all right, all right.
Yeah, I'll be there. OK.

54
00:06:19,380 --> 00:06:21,548
Joon, dinner!

55
00:06:31,642 --> 00:06:34,103
Spaghetti and salad?

56
00:06:34,269 --> 00:06:36,355
In that order?

57
00:06:38,023 --> 00:06:40,651
What happened between you and Mrs. Smail?

58
00:06:41,777 --> 00:06:44,822
She was given to fits of
semiprecious metaphors.

59
00:06:44,988 --> 00:06:47,658
She's a housekeeper,
not an English professor.

60
00:06:47,825 --> 00:06:49,118
She moves things.

61
00:06:50,244 --> 00:06:52,663
She said you wandered off.

62
00:06:52,830 --> 00:06:54,206
Did you leave the house alone?

63
00:06:55,541 --> 00:06:57,501
Define "alone".

64
00:06:57,668 --> 00:07:00,921
You know full well what I'm talkin' about.

65
00:07:01,505 --> 00:07:07,177
I can't be worried about you knocking
another housekeeper into retirement.

66
00:07:07,344 --> 00:07:09,596
First, it was Mrs. Larkspur.

67
00:07:09,763 --> 00:07:12,099
A woman deeply and hygienically disturbed.

68
00:07:13,308 --> 00:07:16,937
- Her hair smelled.
- But then it was Mrs. Piltz.

69
00:07:17,771 --> 00:07:20,566
Piltz?
The answer's in the question.

70
00:07:23,402 --> 00:07:27,531
Let's face it, Benjamin.
Hiring housekeepers is not your forte.

71
00:07:27,698 --> 00:07:30,701
Well, until I do find another housekeeper,

72
00:07:30,868 --> 00:07:33,495
you are gonna stick close to the house.

73
00:07:33,662 --> 00:07:35,747
Understand?

74
00:07:37,499 --> 00:07:42,212
Now have some salad. By the way, I want
you to come with me to my poker game.

75
00:07:43,881 --> 00:07:46,717
- Benny...
- Come on. You'll have a good time.

76
00:08:29,801 --> 00:08:31,887
Web belt and buckle.

77
00:08:33,430 --> 00:08:36,517
Classical Greek martini shaker.

78
00:08:36,683 --> 00:08:38,936
Six turkey-feather darts.

79
00:08:39,978 --> 00:08:43,106
I'll see you with a Deanna Durbin album.

80
00:08:43,815 --> 00:08:44,816
Come on.

81
00:08:45,776 --> 00:08:51,031
- And I'll raise you with a stethoscope.
- Does it have little plastic earpieces?

82
00:08:51,198 --> 00:08:55,536
- What do you care? You never win, Mike.
- I don't want 'em stabbin' my eardrums.

83
00:08:55,702 --> 00:08:57,454
Steering-wheel knob.

84
00:08:57,621 --> 00:09:00,332
Salad Shooter.

85
00:09:01,333 --> 00:09:03,585
'56 Plymouth tire iron.

86
00:09:03,752 --> 00:09:07,464
- Fold-0.
- You must have a good hand?

87
00:09:08,674 --> 00:09:10,217
No, I'm bluffin'.

88
00:09:12,427 --> 00:09:13,762
Really?

89
00:09:16,473 --> 00:09:18,892
Come on.
You gotta play to find out.

90
00:09:19,059 --> 00:09:23,146
OK. 150 feet of coaxial cable.
Show 'em.

91
00:09:23,313 --> 00:09:26,984
- Full house. Jacks over fours.
- Shit.

92
00:09:29,945 --> 00:09:31,196
I thought he was bluffin'.

93
00:09:32,197 --> 00:09:34,658
Will someone get some air to his brain?

94
00:09:34,825 --> 00:09:36,201
He was bluffing about bluffing.

95
00:09:37,744 --> 00:09:39,746
You're a real pal, Benny.

96
00:09:39,913 --> 00:09:44,167
I got a solution to your housekeeper
problem. You can have my roommate.

97
00:09:44,334 --> 00:09:49,339
That's a terrific offer, Benjamin.
Save you from the chore of Smail shopping.

98
00:09:49,506 --> 00:09:51,800
Those places are such drudgery.

99
00:09:51,967 --> 00:09:55,387
Montgomery and Smails,
Smails and Roebuck, Smails-R-Us...

100
00:09:55,554 --> 00:09:56,763
Joon.

101
00:09:58,348 --> 00:10:01,935
- When did you get a roommate?
- Since last week.

102
00:10:02,102 --> 00:10:06,607
My cousin pounded into town and life's
gone from heaven to hell in seven days.

103
00:10:07,691 --> 00:10:11,653
- Just like the good Lord intended.
- 26 years old, he can't even read.

104
00:10:11,820 --> 00:10:14,323
Spends all day polishing my plastic forks.

105
00:10:14,489 --> 00:10:17,868
When you say he can't read,
what do you mean? Like words?

106
00:10:18,035 --> 00:10:22,039
Yeah. And he keeps me up all night
watchin' stupid old movies.

107
00:10:22,205 --> 00:10:23,665
My work's starting to suffer.

108
00:10:23,832 --> 00:10:25,709
You install cable TV.

109
00:10:25,876 --> 00:10:28,879
Joon, will you please glue your sequins?

110
00:10:30,714 --> 00:10:34,051
Have we an internal sequin issue
to deal with, Benjamin?

111
00:10:34,885 --> 00:10:37,554
All right, can we make this the last hand?

112
00:10:41,266 --> 00:10:43,393
Come on, come on.
Play cards.

113
00:10:45,562 --> 00:10:49,107
Two tickets,
tomorrow night's baseball game.

114
00:10:50,400 --> 00:10:52,736
One Pocket Fisherman.

115
00:10:53,612 --> 00:10:55,947
- Fold.
- Do you ever stay in?

116
00:11:00,619 --> 00:11:02,704
Snorkel mask.

117
00:12:10,105 --> 00:12:12,441
She knows how to rattle the day help.

118
00:12:12,607 --> 00:12:16,862
I think we need to find someone
more understanding than Mrs. Smail.

119
00:12:17,612 --> 00:12:19,906
Tell me, how are you two getting along?

120
00:12:20,073 --> 00:12:21,992
Us?

121
00:12:22,159 --> 00:12:25,078
Fine. Normal.
You know, fine.

122
00:12:25,245 --> 00:12:27,164
- Why?
- I'll level with you.

123
00:12:27,330 --> 00:12:31,418
I think it's time you gave some
serious consideration to a group home.

124
00:12:33,086 --> 00:12:36,590
- She already has a home.
- Benny, she'd be with her peers.

125
00:12:36,757 --> 00:12:41,136
She hates her peers.
She's quit the two day centers to prove it.

126
00:12:41,303 --> 00:12:44,014
Look, all we need right now
is a new housekeeper.

127
00:12:44,181 --> 00:12:48,185
Well, I know of no one else.
You've been up and down the list.

128
00:12:48,351 --> 00:12:51,438
You might want to consider that
there are some people

129
00:12:51,605 --> 00:12:54,566
more capable of handling
these episodes than you.

130
00:12:57,360 --> 00:13:01,698
I think that you two living together
may not be the best thing any more.

131
00:13:03,200 --> 00:13:06,203
I'm her brother, and I'm her only family.

132
00:13:06,369 --> 00:13:10,624
And we've done just fine,
the two of us, for 12 years.

133
00:13:10,791 --> 00:13:16,630
Yes, but her stress level is always
a factor in her display of symptoms.

134
00:13:16,797 --> 00:13:19,966
Her agitation should be kept to a minimum.

135
00:13:20,133 --> 00:13:23,261
Everybody gets agitated.
Sometimes it's the only option.

136
00:13:23,428 --> 00:13:25,764
Benny, don't get me wrong.

137
00:13:25,931 --> 00:13:28,225
I'm impressed how
you've managed this long.

138
00:13:29,643 --> 00:13:32,979
But a group home would let her
develop other relationships.

139
00:13:33,146 --> 00:13:37,150
We don't know this,
but what if she were capable of a job?

140
00:13:37,317 --> 00:13:39,778
They'd encourage her in that direction.

141
00:13:39,945 --> 00:13:44,616
These are very nice places...
nurturing, supportive.

142
00:13:44,783 --> 00:13:46,868
I'm not farming her out.

143
00:14:11,309 --> 00:14:14,479
I have every right to be outside, Officer.

144
00:14:14,646 --> 00:14:16,731
- I have every right.
- Yes, ma'am.

145
00:14:17,357 --> 00:14:19,025
May I see some ID, please?

146
00:14:33,456 --> 00:14:35,166
Waldo, did you start that brake job yet?

147
00:14:35,333 --> 00:14:38,461
Joon called.
You've run out of tapioca.

148
00:14:38,628 --> 00:14:42,173
- She what?
- And the police will corroborate.

149
00:14:44,259 --> 00:14:46,344
Holy shit.

150
00:14:48,263 --> 00:14:51,683
Listen, Jack, you wanna go
to the baseball game tonight?

151
00:14:51,850 --> 00:14:54,144
- Hey, thanks, Benny.
- Box seats.

152
00:14:57,689 --> 00:14:59,774
Hello?
Joon?

153
00:15:15,999 --> 00:15:18,084
Time for your medicine, Joon.

154
00:16:19,229 --> 00:16:21,314
Good night, Steve.

155
00:16:31,825 --> 00:16:36,287
- Hello. How's it goin'?
- I appreciate the deal on the engine.

156
00:16:36,830 --> 00:16:40,750
- No problem. Is it runnin' all right?
- Yeah, it's running great.

157
00:16:40,917 --> 00:16:43,461
- Good.
- So... can I...

158
00:16:43,628 --> 00:16:46,131
Can I make it up to you with some dinner?

159
00:16:47,340 --> 00:16:49,009
Some dinner?

160
00:16:49,592 --> 00:16:52,846
- Are you serious?
- Yeah. Dinner with you.

161
00:16:56,349 --> 00:16:58,560
You know what?
I can't.

162
00:16:58,727 --> 00:17:01,062
- I mean, I'd like to...
- It's OK.

163
00:17:01,229 --> 00:17:03,314
OK.

164
00:17:06,943 --> 00:17:09,029
Stupid.
Stupid.

165
00:17:22,584 --> 00:17:25,045
- 18-15.
- 17-16.

166
00:17:25,211 --> 00:17:27,714
- 18-15!
- It caught the corner.

167
00:17:28,256 --> 00:17:31,092
- It was a foot off the table.
- It was not.

168
00:17:31,259 --> 00:17:33,303
- Juniper...
- Benjamin...

169
00:17:33,470 --> 00:17:36,973
Don't underestimate the mentally ill.
We know how to count.

170
00:17:37,140 --> 00:17:42,312
- OK, fine. 17-16.
- You can't give me what was mine.

171
00:17:42,479 --> 00:17:44,731
- You're trying to cheat.
- I'm not.

172
00:17:44,898 --> 00:17:47,984
- You're cheating.
- Joon, you're the one who's cheating.

173
00:17:48,151 --> 00:17:50,361
You're all trying to cheat me.
You're trying to cheat.

174
00:18:05,752 --> 00:18:09,756
Yeah. I spoke to some of the guys
on the staff, Benny.

175
00:18:09,923 --> 00:18:12,092
Nobody wants to be a housekeeper.

176
00:18:14,135 --> 00:18:19,307
I will. I'll keep tryin'. But I gotta
tell you honestly, I don't think so.

177
00:18:19,474 --> 00:18:22,143
Yeah. OK.
Thanks.

178
00:18:22,310 --> 00:18:24,395
Bye.

179
00:19:05,103 --> 00:19:07,188
OK, Stevie.

180
00:19:36,301 --> 00:19:40,680
I mean, I can't even keep a goldfish alive.
What chance do I have with Joon?

181
00:19:41,389 --> 00:19:44,100
If somethin' bad happened to her, I'd...

182
00:19:46,060 --> 00:19:49,230
I'd never ever be able to forgive myself.

183
00:19:49,397 --> 00:19:52,358
A group home
is the right thing for her, Benny.

184
00:19:52,525 --> 00:19:55,528
Yeah.
This is definitely for her own good.

185
00:19:57,405 --> 00:20:00,200
Hey, it's for both your own good.

186
00:20:00,909 --> 00:20:03,536
How much longer
can you do this to yourself?

187
00:20:03,703 --> 00:20:06,206
Your life is literally passing you by.

188
00:20:08,541 --> 00:20:09,959
You're right.

189
00:20:11,294 --> 00:20:14,005
You're right.
What am I doing with myself?

190
00:20:15,548 --> 00:20:19,594
I spend my life workin' on cars
and takin' care of my sister.

191
00:20:19,761 --> 00:20:22,597
I can't have a relationship
without havin' to worry

192
00:20:22,764 --> 00:20:25,141
about how Joon is gonna fit in.

193
00:20:25,308 --> 00:20:28,853
Once she gets settled in,
you could actually take a vacation.

194
00:20:29,020 --> 00:20:31,564
Travel a little.
I can hold down the fort.

195
00:20:31,731 --> 00:20:33,316
Travel?

196
00:20:34,776 --> 00:20:36,319
Travel?

197
00:20:36,486 --> 00:20:39,405
Benny, there's a whole world out there.

198
00:20:39,572 --> 00:20:42,242
I mean, picture yourself on the open road.

199
00:20:42,408 --> 00:20:44,911
Wind in the hair in the El Camino.

200
00:20:45,078 --> 00:20:47,372
Highway stretchin' out.

201
00:20:47,538 --> 00:20:49,624
What's that, up ahead?

202
00:20:50,458 --> 00:20:52,669
A lovely motorist, stranded.

203
00:20:52,835 --> 00:20:55,922
Carburetor trouble.
Better investigate.

204
00:20:56,089 --> 00:20:59,300
Yeah, right.
I'm gonna be stoppin' every 15 minutes

205
00:20:59,467 --> 00:21:01,886
to call Joon to see how she's doin'.

206
00:21:04,389 --> 00:21:08,142
OK, let's see.
Black Sabbath, over there.

207
00:21:08,309 --> 00:21:11,604
- Is that a flashlight?
- It's a brush kind of a thing.

208
00:21:11,771 --> 00:21:13,731
Here's a hat.

209
00:21:13,898 --> 00:21:16,776
- Where's the batteries?
- You didn't win batteries.

210
00:21:16,943 --> 00:21:20,154
- Those are mine.
- OK. Hey, guys, hurry it up!

211
00:21:20,321 --> 00:21:22,782
Or we'll start without you.

212
00:21:22,949 --> 00:21:25,076
I've been known to play a little cards.

213
00:21:45,847 --> 00:21:47,932
Box of 30-aught-6 cartridges.

214
00:21:52,770 --> 00:21:55,106
Medium-sized, green-haired troll.

215
00:21:56,316 --> 00:21:58,484
Soap-on-a-rope, slightly used.

216
00:22:01,362 --> 00:22:03,448
- Cards?
- Three.

217
00:22:04,490 --> 00:22:06,576
- Cards?
- Two.

218
00:22:07,535 --> 00:22:09,620
And the dealer takes...

219
00:22:10,330 --> 00:22:12,415
three.

220
00:22:16,294 --> 00:22:17,420
Pass.

221
00:22:20,506 --> 00:22:22,633
Re-grout my shower.
Blue grout.

222
00:22:23,926 --> 00:22:25,511
I fold.

223
00:22:28,306 --> 00:22:30,391
Shampoo my dog.

224
00:22:30,975 --> 00:22:33,061
Lava lamp.

225
00:22:35,688 --> 00:22:37,940
Paint the exterior of my house.

226
00:22:38,107 --> 00:22:40,193
Hey, come on, slow down.

227
00:22:40,360 --> 00:22:42,195
This is supposed to be reasonable stakes.

228
00:22:42,362 --> 00:22:46,074
That's a see and a raise.
You follow me?

229
00:22:51,954 --> 00:22:56,125
- You take my cousin off my hands.
- Wait, wait, wait. Just stop.

230
00:22:56,292 --> 00:23:00,129
- Benny's gonna strangle you guys.
- Chill out, Thomas.

231
00:23:02,965 --> 00:23:05,510
- Joon, we gotta go.
- Flush!

232
00:23:10,139 --> 00:23:12,642
Full house.

233
00:23:13,476 --> 00:23:15,478
Yes.
Yes!

234
00:23:15,645 --> 00:23:19,982
- Benny, tonight's your lucky night.
- Mike warned her it was for keeps.

235
00:23:20,149 --> 00:23:22,485
What?
What was for keeps?

236
00:23:24,112 --> 00:23:25,488
I lost.

237
00:23:26,489 --> 00:23:30,660
- What's in the pot?
- A cousin.

238
00:24:00,106 --> 00:24:03,651
Rules are rules. Without 'em
there's no order in the universe.

239
00:24:03,818 --> 00:24:06,863
Don't you give me that crap.
You took advantage.

240
00:24:07,029 --> 00:24:11,617
Of your sick sister. A heart flush
